This paper deals with the representation and manipulation of belief functions, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of consistent transformations in reasoning processes is a technique that is commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses distance measures and norms, which are concepts that are relevant to data science (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI).
